==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ˈskei.biz/
*Other 1: (skāʹbēz)
*Other 2: SKAY-beez
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪbiz|-eɪbiz]]
===Noun===
'''scabies'''
# {{pathology}} An infestation of parasitic [[mite]]s, ''Sarcoptes scabiei'', causing intense itching caused by the mites burrowing into the skin of humans and other animals. It is easily transmissible from human to human; secondary skin infection may occur.

